          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h1 id=\"nyc-traffic-fatality-analysis-vision-zero-policy-brief\">NYC Traffic Fatality Analysis \u2014 Vision Zero Policy Brief</h1>\n<span class=\"paragraph\"><strong>Project Lead:</strong> Remy Ndayizeye<br />\n<strong>Context:</strong> Northeast Big Data Innovation Hub \u00b7 National Student Data Corps<br />\n<strong>Date:</strong> May 2026</span>\n<hr />\n<h2 id=\"executive-summary-the-lethality-paradox\">Executive Summary: The Lethality Paradox</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">NYC reached a historic safety milestone in 2025 with 205 traffic deaths\u2014the lowest count since 1910. \nHowever, a critical <strong>\"Lethality Paradox\"</strong> has emerged: while total crashes are down, the likelihood of a crash \nbeing fatal has increased since 2020. This analysis utilizes a <strong>Recency-Weighted Hybrid Model</strong> to distinguish between chronic infrastructure failures and emerging behavioral crises.</span>\n<hr />\n<span class=\"paragraph\"><strong>Data Source:</strong> NYC Open Data \u2014 1.95M crashes (July 2012 \u2013 April 2026)</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
